# Project constraints

- Build only the configured SF waterfront MVP; never expand scope implicitly.
- Never use Google map, Street View, 3D Tiles, or scraped Google data.
- Keep runtime map use offline and preserve source attribution metadata.
- Use deterministic generation and stable IDs.
- Keep `PROJECT_STATE.md` honest after meaningful phases.
- Run formatting, static checks, and tests before marking a phase complete.
- Do not claim Unreal compiled unless a real Unreal build command succeeded.
- Do not begin a later milestone while current critical acceptance gates fail.
